title: the myth of 'productivity'
description:
We have been sold a version of success that requires us to be productive every single waking hour of our day. That is the myth of productivity. Join me as I discuss it playing Terraria.

Between the pressures of a 9-to-5 job and the hustle culture we see online everywhere, it feels like we are holding ourselves to a standard that is simply impossible to maintain at least in my opinion.

In my eight episode (I think), I am discussing the myth of constant productivity and why I am choosing to lower my daily expectations in favour of actual progress.

I talk about the guilt of doing nothing (we all face) and how our obsession with output is actually making us less effective at building the lives we want. 

Instead of chasing a perfect routine, I am looking for pockets of peace in a corporate world that seems relentless. This is a ramble about honestly just reclaiming your time from the pressure of always having to be a switched on.

title: Is More Productivity Always Better? Economic Tradeoffs of Modern Livestock Breeds
description:
🐄📈 What if producing more isn’t always the same as earning more? In “Is More Productivity Always Better? Economic Tradeoffs of Modern Livestock Breeds,” we unpack the hidden economics behind today’s high-yield animals—and the tough choices farmers face when chasing maximum output.

Modern livestock breeds can grow faster, produce more milk, or lay more eggs than ever before. But higher productivity often comes with higher feed bills, rising veterinary costs, tighter management demands, and greater vulnerability to market swings.

In this video, you’ll discover:
• 🧬 Why modern livestock breeds were selected for extreme productivity
• 💸 How higher yields can also mean higher feed, health, and care costs
• 🏥 Why veterinary dependence increases as genetics become more specialized
• 📉 How market volatility can turn high-output systems into high-risk systems
• 🌍 Real farmer experiences balancing productivity with resilience
• 🔄 Why some farms are reintroducing hardier or mixed-breed systems

Whether you raise cattle, poultry, pigs, or small ruminants, this episode challenges the assumption that “more is always better” and explores how profitability, animal welfare, and long-term resilience are deeply connected.

👉 Stay until the end to see how future breeding strategies may focus less on maximum output—and more on efficiency, health, and adaptability in an uncertain world.

Saltwind Notation — ambient piano and wind textures. Perfect for deep focus, exam prep, sleep, and productivity.
